<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">The things I look for in a case:
<br />

<br />
- Quiet Fans.
<br />
- Space for at least 2 more drives than you are actually planning on using.
<br />
- Easy access.  (thumbscrews, etc..)
<br />
- Front and rear fans.
<br />
- Powerful power supply.  (I sometimes have up to 4 IDE/SCSI drives.)
<br />

<br />
The features that I don't really care much for:
<br />

<br />
- Jacks on the front of the case.  (I rarely need them and I use my laptop for things like my digital camera anyhow.)
<br />
- Window on the side.
<br />
- LEDs or temperature sensors.
<br />
- More than two 5.25" disk drives.
<br />
- Non-Removable mobo tray.  (those things annoy me)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
